    About
    stephenking.com

    Description

    Stephen Edwin King is an American author of horror, supernatural fiction, suspense, crime, science-fiction, and fantasy novels. Described as the "King of Horror", his books have sold more than 350 million copies as of 2006, and many have been adapted into films, television series, miniseries, and comic books. Wikipedia
    Born: September 21, 1947 (age 75 years), Portland, ME
    Children: Joe Hill, Naomi King, Owen King
    Spouse: Tabitha King (m. 1971)
    Influenced by: H. P. Lovecraft, Edgar Allan Poe, J. R. R. Tolkien, MORE
    Parents: Donald Edwin King, Nellie Ruth Pillsbury King
